Title: Series: Aerdige Lantschappen Geteeckent door Herman van Swanevelt (Landscapes after Herman van Swanevelt)
Description: Plate 9: Mountainous landscape with Joseph reclining at centre next to the grazing ass; reduced copy in reverse of a detail after Herman van Swanevelt (Virgin and Child missing) Etching
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of twelve, for comment see F,2.232. For impressions of the original by Swanevelt in BM and for comment see S.2276.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (9) (copy)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (monogram with date 1791)
